==Demographics==
Since 1900, the population has never fallen below 300 or risen above 600, reaching a peak of 590 in the 1920s. Today about 480 people reside in Ulen, making it one of over 12,000 incorporated places in the United States with fewer than 2,500 citizens, the population below which the US Census Bureau defines an area to be rural.<ref name="Cederström 2018 376–402"/> As of 2022 the town of Ulen has the 8th highest amount of [[Norwegian Americans]], relative to its total population, in the state of [[Minnesota]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/profile?g=1600000US2766136 |access-date=2023-01-13 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref>{{US Census population
